<HEAD>Former Nuremberg War Crimes Prosecutor Dead At Age 77</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American lawyer who served on
the prosecution team at the Nazi war crimes trials in Nuremberg
after World War II has died, his law office said.
   The Frankfurt law firm of O'Haire, Fiore and von Maur said Walter
W. O'Haire died of heart failure Thursday. He was 77.
   O'Haire was born in Pittston, Pa., and served in the U.S. Army
until he joined the Nuremberg prosecution team in 1946, the
statement said.
   It said O'Haire set up the American law firm in Frankfurt in 1950.
   The statement said O'Haire would be buried in his native Pittston
on Dec. 16. No other details were immediately available.
