defense spending is _
   Q: If Soviet troop posture leads to some cuts on our own and that
this would help to reduce the deficit. People are already looking,
some Democrats, thinking that this may help us to reduce the deficit.
   A: Well, once again, I must repeat, that can't happen with our
defense spending until we have reached a parity and at which then
both sides can continue the reduction of weapons and keeping it at a
parity. But, that is not true today. They _ the dropping of 500,000
military personnel still leaves them with five million under arms.
They have _ they still outnumber us in tanks and artillery weapons
after they make these cuts. So, we haven't achieved parity, but at
least, if he goes through with that and succeeds in that, he is
going to bring it down to a range where I think that he would see
that we could proceed and continue, then mutually reducing arms
between each other.
   THE PRESS: Thank you, Mr. President. Merry Christmas.
   THE PRESIDENT: Thank you. Merry Christmas to you all.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>END TEXT, 9 TAKES.</HEAD>
