<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--CIAProtester     12-09 0157</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--CIA Protester,0161</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Student Arrested After Taking Officer's Gun</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADISON, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A University of Wisconsin student was
arrested after taking a police officer's gun and urging fellow
demonstrators to cross a police line to protest CIA job recruiting,
authorities said.
   James C. Carl, 26, was arrested Thursday and put in jail on
tentative charges of disorderly conduct, resisting arrest and
disarming a police officer, police said.
   Carl was among 25 demonstrators who tried to interrupt job
recruiting appointments by the Central Intelligence Agency at the
university's College of Engineering. CIA representatives make annual
visits to the university and other campuses around the country.
   Carl was arrested while urging other protesters to break through
a police line, said university police and security Sgt. David
Williams.
   The student removed a revolver from an officer's holster during a
struggle with officers attempting to arrest him for disorderly
conduct, Williams said.
   There were no injuries or other arrests.
</TEXT>
