<1ST_LINE>r a PM-PTL-Tammy-Sally     12-09 0287</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-PTL-Tammy-Sally,0294</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tammy Bakker Calls Charges Against Her Husband `Lies'</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PAUL NOWELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PINEVILLE, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former television preacher's allegations
that he had sex with PTL founder Jim Bakker are ``lies'' from a
``former good friend,'' Tammy Faye Bakker says.
   Mrs. Bakker denied the charges against her husband by John Wesley
Fletcher, a former co-host of ``The PTL Club,'' in an interview
Thursday with TV talk show host Sally Jessy Raphael.
   ``I've lived with this man for 27 years and I know he's not
(bisexual),'' Mrs. Bakker said during the show.
   Mrs. Bakker agreed to appear on the show after Raphael promised
not to do a planned show with Fletcher, said Burt Dubrow, executive
producer of the ``Sally Jessy Raphael Show.'' The interview with
Mrs. Bakker will be aired Dec. 19.
   Fletcher, who appeared on ``The PTL Club'' from the mid-1970s to
1981, said in an interview for January's Penthouse magazine: ``I was
Jim Bakker's male prostitute.'' Bakker, who was indicted this week
on federal charges of wire and mail fraud and conspiracy, has denied
in a sworn deposition that he has ever had a homosexual
relationship, and has denied charges of financial wrongdoing.
   Bakker resigned from PTL in March 1987 after admitting he had a
sexual encounter with church secretary Jessica Hahn and paying her
hush money.
   With her husband watching the taping on a tiny monitor in the
driveway outside the couple's leased 14-room log cabin, Mrs. Bakker
talked about the pain she has suffered during the past two years,
including being humiliated when people at shopping malls and
restaurants ridiculed her and her husband.
   ``Sometimes I wish we could just move away to another planet,''
she said tearfully.
</TEXT>
