<HEAD>Group Trapped By Floodwaters Rescued After Five Days</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUOTATHAL, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Floodwaters trapped 19 cave
explorers nearly 2,000 feet underground for five days before they
were rescued unharmed, the expedition leader said.
   Rescuers used rubber rafts to ferry the 14 youths, aged 11 to 18,
and five adult guides to safety Thursday night.
   The group entered Hoelloch, one of Europe's largest systems of
underground caverns and pools, for a one-day tour Saturday but was
cut off when heavy rain flooded part of the cave system.
   The spelunkers, well-equipped with food and camping equipment,
retreated to a dry spot about 2,000 feet underground.
   Expedition leader Max Gubser said no one panicked and that that
all members were unhurt after the ordeal.
