<HEAD>Christmas Carol Festival Canceled Because of Whites-Only Law</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOKSBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A yearly multiracial Christmas
carol festival has been canceled because the lakeside park where it
would be held has been declared a ``whites only'' area, organizers
said Friday.
   The sing has taken place at Boksburg Lake, the main park in this
industrial town east of Johannesburg, for four years, but the
far-right Conservative Party administration that just took over has
resegregated the park. The Boksburg Publicity Association said it
canceled the event because of that.
   Conservatives won control of the Boksburg council and dozens of
others in local elections Oct. 26. The Boksburg council voted to
restore ``whites only'' status to the town hall, park and other
facilities that were open to all races in recent years.
   Anti-apartheid leaders, business groups and the governing
National Party denouced the action, and blacks have begun a consumer
boycott of white-owned stores. Several government officials who
criticized the Conservatives come from cities where beaches,
libraries and swimming pools are segregated.
