<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--NBC Cutbacks,0132</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>NBC To Lay Off 56 Staff Engineers in Burbank</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NBC will lay off 56 network staff
engineers at its Burbank studios in February and June, the network
announced Friday.
   In the first step, 30 engineers will be cut by Feb. 17, and in
the sefcond 26 more will be laid off by June 16.
   NBC is offering sizable bonuses to engineers who volunteer for
layoff. The cutbacks are in operations and technical services, which
supply floor cameramen, lighting directors, technical directors and
videotape editors.
   The layoffs are in addition to a cutback of 90 engineers in New
York, 24 in Chicago, 13 in Washington, D.C., and three in Cleveland.
   NBC said the layoffs were the result of innovations in videotape
technology.
