<NOTE>For Release Sunday, Dec. 18, and Thereafter</NOTE>
<HEAD>Song Sings Praises of Potato</HEAD>
<HEAD>With Potato-Ireland, b0786</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are a few lines from an Irish song
about potatoes, attributed to Robert Owenson (1744-1812):
   In the land of potatoes, O!
   Hospitality
   All reality,
   No formality,
   There you ever see;
   But free and easy
   'Twould so amaze ye,
   You'd think us all crazy,
   For dull we never be.
</TEXT>
