<DOCNO> AP881209-0208 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-09-88 1120EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-UniversalFoods     12-09 0139</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Universal Foods,0145</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Food Proessing Company Rejects Takeover Bid By Massachusetts Firm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Universal Foods Corp. has rejected a takeover
bid by a Massachusetts company valued at more than $500 million in
cash.
   The food processing company said Thursday its board voted
unanimously to turn down a $30.50 a share offer by Amanda
Acquisition Corp., a subsidiary of High Voltage Engineering Corp. of
Burlington, Mass.
   Universal has 16.5 million shares outstanding.
   In a statement, Universal said its board ``reaffirmed its
commitment to remain an independent company pursuing its current
highly successful business plan.''
   Universal rose 75 cents to $33.75 Thursday on the New York Stock
Exchange.
   Universal Chairman John Murray said the company would fight a
lawsuit filed by Amanda Dec. 2 in U.S. District Court in Milwaukee
seeking to overturn anti-takeover measures adopted by Universal.
</TEXT>
