<HEAD>Agriculture Department Inspector General Quits</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert W. Beuley, the Agriculture Department's
inspector general for more than two years, has resigned effective
Dec. 26, his office said Friday.
   No plans were announced, except that Beuley expects to go to work
in the private sector here.
   Beuley, 49, became USDA's inspector general, or internal
watchdog, in August 1986. He joined the department as deputy in
September 1985. Before that he was assistant inspector general for
auditing at the Interior Department for five years and had also
served in the Commerce Depaertment.
