<HEAD>Ford Boosting and Extending Rebates; GM Extends Gas Giveaway on
Some Olds</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. boosted some incentives and extended others after
other automakers made similar moves earlier this week, while General
Motors Corp. extended an offer of free gasoline for some car buyers,
the companies said Friday.
   New Ford incentives ranged from $300 to $3,000 and expire in
January or February, depending on the model of car and where it is
purchased.
   ``The increases are in response to the additional incentives
announced by our competitors earlier this week,'' said Robert Rewey,
vice president for Ford's North American Sales Operations.
   Meantime, GM's Oldsmobile Division said it was extending its
offer for a year's free gasoline from Nov. 31 to Dec. 31 for some
Cutlass Supreme buyers.
   The offer is good for buyers of 1988 and 1989 models purchased in
Oldsmobile's East Region, comprising 15 states and the District of
Columbia.
